05167 union cvmx_endor_rfif_1pps_sample_cnt_offset {
05168     uint32_t u32;
05169     struct cvmx_endor_rfif_1pps_sample_cnt_offset_s {
05170 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
05171     uint32_t reserved_20_31               : 12;
05172     uint32_t offset                       : 20; /**< This register holds the sample count at which the 1PPS
05173                                                          was received.
05174                                                          Upon reset, the sample counter starts at 0 when the
05175                                                          first 1PPS is received and then increments to wrap
05176                                                          around at FRAME_L-1. At each subsequent 1PPS, a
05177                                                          snapshot of the sample counter is taken and the count
05178                                                          is made available via this register. This enables
05179                                                          software to monitor the RF clock drift relative to
05180                                                          the 1PPS. */
05181 #else

05183     uint32_t reserved_20_31               : 12;
05184 #endif
05185     } s;

05231 /**
05232  * cvmx_endor_rfif_conf
05233  */
05234 union cvmx_endor_rfif_conf {
05235     uint32_t u32;
05236     struct cvmx_endor_rfif_conf_s {
05237 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
05238     uint32_t reserved_18_31               : 14;
05239     uint32_t loopback                     : 1;  /**< FDD loop back mode
05240                                                          - 0: Not in loopback mode(default)
05241                                                          - 1: loops back the tx ouput to the rx input inside the
05242                                                           rf_if */
05243     uint32_t mol                          : 1;  /**< Manual Override Lock */
05244     uint32_t upd_style                    : 1;  /**< TX and RX Windows parameters update style (default:0)
05245                                                          - 0: updated as written to the register (on the fly)
05246                                                           (not fully verified but kept in case limitations are
05247                                                           found with the other update scheme.)
05248                                                          - 1: updated at the specified time by registers 00F and
05249                                                           90F.
05250                                                           Note the frame length is updated after the last TX
05251                                                           window.
05252                                                          - 1: eNB, enables using 1PPS synchronization scheme. */
05253     uint32_t diversity                    : 1;  /**< RX diversity disable (Used to support FDD SISO with CLK
05254                                                           4X)
05255                                                          - 0: Data gets written to the diversity FIFO in MIMO mode
05256                                                           (default).
05257                                                          - 1: No data written to the diversity FIFO in MIMO mode. */
05258     uint32_t duplex                       : 1;  /**< Division Duplex Mode
05259                                                          - 0: TDD (default)
05260                                                          - 1: FDD */
05261     uint32_t prod_type                    : 1;  /**< Product Type
05262                                                          - 0: UE (default), enables using sync and timing advance
05263                                                           synchronization schemes. */
05264     uint32_t txnrx_ctrl                   : 1;  /**< RFIC IF TXnRX signal pulse control. Changing the value
05265                                                          of this bit generates a pulse on the TXNRX signal of
05266                                                          the RFIC interface. This feature is enabled when bit
05267                                                          9 has already been asserted. */
05268     uint32_t ena_ctrl                     : 1;  /**< RFIC IF ENABLE signal pulse control. Changing the value
05269                                                          of this bit generates a pulse on the ENABLE signal of
05270                                                          the RFIC interface. This feature is enabled when bit 9
05271                                                          has already been asserted. */
05272     uint32_t man_ctrl                     : 1;  /**< RF IC Manual Control Enable. Setting this bit to 1
05273                                                          enables manual control of the TXNRX and ENABLE signals.
05274                                                          When set to 0 (default), the TXNRX and ENABLE signals
05275                                                          are automatically controlled when opening and closing
05276                                                          RX/TX windows. The manual mode is used to initialize
05277                                                          the RFIC in alert mode. */
05278     uint32_t dsp_rx_int_en                : 1;  /**< DSP RX interrupt mask enable
05279                                                          - 0: DSP RX receives interrupts
05280                                                          - 1: DSP RX doesn't receive interrupts, needs to poll
05281                                                           ISRs */
05282     uint32_t adi_en                       : 1;  /**< ADI enable signal pulsed or leveled behavior
05283                                                          - 0: pulsed
05284                                                          - 1: leveled */
05285     uint32_t clr_fifo_of                  : 1;  /**< Clear RX FIFO overflow flag. */
05286     uint32_t clr_fifo_ur                  : 1;  /**< Clear RX FIFO under run flag. */
05287     uint32_t wavesat_mode                 : 1;  /**< AD9361 wavesat mode, where enable becomes rx_control
05288                                                           and txnrx becomes tx_control. The wavesat mode permits
05289                                                           an independent control of the rx and tx data flows.
05290                                                          - 0: wavesat mode
05291                                                          - 1: regular mode */
05292     uint32_t flush                        : 1;  /**< Flush RX FIFO auto clear register. */
05293     uint32_t inv                          : 1;  /**< Data inversion (bit 0 becomes bit 11, bit 1 becomes 10) */
05294     uint32_t mode                         : 1;  /**< 0: SISO 1: MIMO */
05295     uint32_t enable                       : 1;  /**< 1=enable, 0=disabled */
05296 #else
05297     uint32_t enable                       : 1;
05298     uint32_t mode                         : 1;
05299     uint32_t inv                          : 1;
05300     uint32_t flush                        : 1;
05301     uint32_t wavesat_mode                 : 1;
05302     uint32_t clr_fifo_ur                  : 1;
05303     uint32_t clr_fifo_of                  : 1;
05304     uint32_t adi_en                       : 1;
05305     uint32_t dsp_rx_int_en                : 1;
05306     uint32_t man_ctrl                     : 1;
05307     uint32_t ena_ctrl                     : 1;
05308     uint32_t txnrx_ctrl                   : 1;
05309     uint32_t prod_type                    : 1;
05310     uint32_t duplex                       : 1;
05311     uint32_t diversity                    : 1;
05312     uint32_t upd_style                    : 1;
05313     uint32_t mol                          : 1;
05314     uint32_t loopback                     : 1;
05315     uint32_t reserved_18_31               : 14;
05316 #endif
05317     } s;
05318     struct cvmx_endor_rfif_conf_s         cnf71xx;
05319 };
05320 typedef union cvmx_endor_rfif_conf cvmx_endor_rfif_conf_t;

06485 /**
06486  * cvmx_endor_rfif_timer64_en
06487  *
06488  * Notes:
06489  * This is how the 64-bit timer works:
06490  * 1- Configuration
06491  *     - Write counter LSB (reg:0x69)
06492  *     - Write counter MSB (reg:0x6A)
06493  *     - Write config (reg:0x68)
06494  * 2- Enable the counter
06495  * 3- Wait for the 1PPS
06496  * 4- Start incrementing the counter every n+1 rf clock cycles
06497  * 5- Read the MSB and LSB registers (reg:0x6B and 0x6C)
06498  *
06499  * 6- There is no 64-bit snapshot mechanism. Software has to consider the
06500  *    32 LSB might rollover and increment the 32 MSB between the LSB and the
06501  *    MSB reads. You may want to use the following concatenation recipe:
06502  *
06503  * a) Read the 32 MSB (MSB1)
06504  * b) Read the 32 LSB
06505  * c) Read the 32 MSB again (MSB2)
06506  * d) Concatenate the 32 MSB an 32 LSB
06507  *      -If both 32 MSB are equal or LSB(31)=1, concatenate MSB1 and LSB
06508  *      -Else concatenate the MSB2 and LSB
06509  */
06510 union cvmx_endor_rfif_timer64_en {
06511     uint32_t u32;
06512     struct cvmx_endor_rfif_timer64_en_s {
06513 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
06514     uint32_t reserved_1_31                : 31;
06515     uint32_t ena                          : 1;  /**< Enable for the 64-bit rf clock based timer.
06516                                                          - 0: Disabled
06517                                                          - 1: Enabled */
06518 #else
06519     uint32_t ena                          : 1;
06520     uint32_t reserved_1_31                : 31;
06521 #endif
06522     } s;
06523     struct cvmx_endor_rfif_timer64_en_s   cnf71xx;
06524 };
06525 typedef union cvmx_endor_rfif_timer64_en cvmx_endor_rfif_timer64_en_t;
06526
